Inspirational singer Sola Allyson has celebrated Ondo State’s ex-Governor, Olusegun Mimiko and his wife, Olukemi Mimiko, saying they delivered her from slave masters in the music industry. Allyson made the revelation while celebrating Mrs. Mimiko on her 53rd birthday on Sunday, June 7. The singer described the governor and his wife as angels in disguise. “Please, please, I want to celebrate Anti Kemi. Please help me! She has been used at notable seasons in my life as help from God! Dr. Mimiko and Anti Kemi were used as instruments of my deliverance from the slave masters of our industry!” she wrote in part of her full tribute to Mrs. Mimiko on her Instagram page.